git tricks for xen-autotest

1. push via ssh while pulling with git url (need higher version git):

(1) : add pushurl in remote section:
[remote "origin"]
        pushurl = git@qe-git.englab.nay.redhat.com:/home/git/repo/yuzhang/xen-autotest

(2) : overwrite the git url for push only
[url "git://qe-git.englab.nay.redhat.com/yuzhang/xen-autotest"]
        pushInsteadOf = git@qe-git.englab.nay.redhat.com:/home/git/repo/yuzhang/xen-autotest


2. Branches management:

(1) On the git server, we have 2 branches: master, virtlab
        $ git branch -a
             * master                # change frequently, unstable
               virtlab               # only used for virtlab

(2) test case developer:
        $ git clone
        $ git branch -b experiment   # Create a local branch
        $ edit, add, commit          # Do local changes 
        $ git checkout master
        $ git pull
        $ git rebase master experiment
        $ git checkout master
        $ git merge experiment       # Fast forward
        ...                          # Push to Server or apply changes to virtlab 

(3) virtlab:
        $ git clone git://qe-git.englab.nay.redhat.com/yuzhang/xen-autotest
        $ git branch -a              # 1 local branch (master), 3 remote branches
        * master
          origin/HEAD
          origin/master
          origin/virtlab

        $ git checkout -b virtlab origin/virtlab
        $ git branch -a              # 1 new local branch added (virtlab)
            master
          * virtlab
            origin/HEAD
            origin/master
            origin/virtlab
        $ git merge master           # merge master into virtlab branch
        $ git push git+ssh://git@qe-git.englab.nay.redhat.com/home/git/repo/yuzhang/xen-autotest virtlab:virtlab # push local virtlab branch to remote server
        # $ git push git+ssh://git@qe-git.englab.nay.redhat.com/home/git/repo/yuzhang/xen-autotest :virtlab # if local branch is ommited, it will delete the remote branch (origin/virtlab)
